<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Blog on Ryan Cranie</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/</link><description>Recent content in Blog on Ryan Cranie</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>thoughts on LinkedIn</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/thoughts-on-linkedin/</link><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/thoughts-on-linkedin/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;-to write-&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>A reflection: EPIC.LAN 43 - 47</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/epiclan-43-47/</link><pubDate>Sun, 22 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/epiclan-43-47/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;-to write-&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>my experience at KEL4</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/kel4-experience/</link><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/kel4-experience/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I have been to six osu! LAN events as of March 2026. But this one, KEL4 in Gdańsk, was my favourite by far.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s something so special about travelling to another country and finding yourself surrounded by people who share this amazing common ground with you. At this point in my life, I don’t think I could’ve asked for a meetup more meaningful. It’s hard to put into words how much it all meant to me.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>VLANs and why I needed to buy an extra switch</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/vlans-extra-switch/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/vlans-extra-switch/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;-to write-&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Build a system that works for you</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/build-a-system/</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/build-a-system/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In the modern world, it’s all too easy to get sucked into technology and waste our lives scrolling on social media. I really sympathize with this, and it affects all of us, regardless of age - whether you’re an iPad kid, a student, an adult with downtime after work, or a senior with nothing else to do. Your relationship with technology is probably something you should be scared of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently, the concept of “dumbifying your phone” and becoming “analog” has surfaced. People buy flip phones, uninstall social medias - however, I mostly disagree with this approach. You’ll just reinstall a few weeks later and realise you can’t do so much nowadays without a smartphone. It’s too integrated into everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>why I try hard and study post graduation</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/why-i-try-hard/</link><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/why-i-try-hard/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;-to write-&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>building phases of my homelab infrastructure</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/homelab-build-phases/</link><pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/homelab-build-phases/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;-to write-&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>March 2026 Music Rotation</title><link>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/march-2026-music/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.ryancranie.com/blog/march-2026-music/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Some cool stuff I have been into this month:&lt;/p&gt;
